Police are appealing for information after the bodies of two children were discovered in Orange Farm, south of Johannesburg, earlier today. The children, aged six and eight, went missing on Friday evening when allegedly walking home from a hair salon. Courtesy#DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police are appealing for information after the bodies of two children were discovered in Orange Farm, south of Johannesburg on Saturday. The children, aged six and eight, went missing on Friday evening when allegedly walking home from a hair salon. READ: Toddler stabbed to death in Orange Farm They were reported missing to the police early Saturday morning. A post mortem will be conducted to determine the cause of death. The double murder investigation is being prioritised and escalated to the provincial investigating unit.